              <h3 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link text-dark text-left w-100 collapsed" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none;" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse8" aria-expanded="false">
                  What electrical requirements do hot tubs need?
                </button>
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div id="collapse8" class="collapse" data-parent="#serviceFAQ">
              <div class="card-body" style="font-size: 15px; color: #555; line-height: 1.7;">
                Most full-size hot tubs require a dedicated 240V/50-amp circuit installed by a licensed electrician. Some smaller models (like the Nordic ALL-IN-110V series) plug into a standard 110V outlet. We'll let you know exactly what your chosen model needs before you buy.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card mb-3 border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-header bg-white" id="faq9">
              <h3 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link text-dark text-left w-100 collapsed" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none;" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse9" aria-expanded="false">
                  How much does a hot tub cost to run monthly?
                </button>
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div id="collapse9" class="collapse" data-parent="#serviceFAQ">
              <div class="card-body" style="font-size: 15px; color: #555; line-height: 1.7;">
                In Utah, most modern hot tubs cost between $20–$50 per month in electricity, depending on the model, insulation quality, and how often you use it. Newer models with full-foam insulation and efficient pumps are on the lower end. A good cover makes a big difference too.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card mb-3 border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-header bg-white" id="faq10">
              <h3 class="mb-0">
                <button class="btn btn-link text-dark text-left w-100 collapsed" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none;" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse10" aria-expanded="false">
                  Can I use a hot tub in winter in Utah?
                </button>
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div id="collapse10" class="collapse" data-parent="#serviceFAQ">
              <div class="card-body" style="font-size: 15px; color: #555; line-height: 1.7;">
                Absolutely — winter is actually the most popular time to use a hot tub in Utah! All the brands we carry are built for cold climates with proper insulation. Just make sure you have a good cover, keep your water chemistry balanced, and never let the tub sit empty in freezing temps.
              </div>
